The paper deals with the transmission of a Gaussian vector source over a Gaussian channel, which is a common topic in information theory (cs.IT). The focus is on the MMSE performance, which is a measure of estimation accuracy, and the paper investigates the necessary conditions for optimal unitary encoders, which falls under the category of matrix factorization and decomposition (cs.MM). The paper also discusses the spread of eigenvalue distribution, which is a topic in linear algebra and spectral theory (cs.LA). The basis dependency of uncertainty in a signal is another key aspect of the paper, which relates to signal processing and machine learning (cs.SP) as well as linear algebra (cs.LA). Finally, the paper presents MMSE bounds that hold with high probability, which is a topic in probability theory and statistics (cs.SI).
